parent={{Created_1.current}}^description="Exterior Inspection: Walk around the aircraft, visually inspecting the exterior for any damage or signs of wear and tear. Inspect the wings, flaps, ailerons, and rudder for any damage or cracks. Check the engines, propellers, and exhaust system for damage or signs of wear.
Interior Inspection: Check the cockpit and cabin for cleanliness and any signs of damage or wear. Avionics: Check the navigation and communication equipment to ensure that they are working properly. Inspect the instruments and gauges for accuracy and proper operation." "Electrical System: Check the battery condition and ensure that it is properly secured. Check the lights and switches to ensure that they are working properly.
Fuel System: Check the fuel level and ensure that it is sufficient for the planned flight. Inspect the fuel tanks, lines, and pumps for any damage or signs of wear.
Hydraulic System: Check the hydraulic fluid level and ensure that it is sufficient for the planned flight. Inspect the hydraulic lines and pumps for any damage or signs of wear." ^assignment_group={{dd62dcfb-890a-41e3-928d-db18c79d08bd.item.u_task_1}}^short_description={{dd62dcfb-890a-41e3-928d-db18c79d08bd.item.u_task_1.name}} Task for {{Created_1.current.maintenance_type}} Aricraft {{Created_1.current.select_aircraft.aircraft_model}}
